    • Method Detail

      • labelGetOrCreateForName

        int labelGetOrCreateForName​(String labelName)
                     throws KernelException
        Returns a label id for a label name. If the label doesn't exist prior to this call it gets created.
        Parameters:
        labelName - the name of the label.
        Returns:
        id of the created label.
        Throws:
        IllegalTokenNameException - if any token name is illegal.
        TokenCapacityExceededKernelException - if too many labels would be created by this call, compared to the token id space available.
        KernelException

      • labelGetOrCreateForNames

        void labelGetOrCreateForNames​(String[] labelNames,
                              int[] labelIds)
                       throws KernelException
        Get or create the label token ids for each of the given labelNames, and store them at the corresponding index in the given labelIds array. This is effectively a batching version of labelGetOrCreateForName(String).
        Parameters:
        labelNames - The array of label names for which to resolve or create their id.
        labelIds - The array into which the resulting token ids will be stored.
        Throws:
        IllegalTokenNameException - if any token name is illegal.
        TokenCapacityExceededKernelException - if too many labels would be created by this call, compared to the token id space available.
        KernelException

      • labelCreateForName

        int labelCreateForName​(String labelName,
                       boolean internal)
                throws KernelException
        Creates a label with the given name.
        Parameters:
        labelName - the name of the label.
        internal - true if the token is internal and must not be visible on the product surface, otherwise false if the token is public.
        Returns:
        id of the created label.
        Throws:
        IllegalTokenNameException - if token name is illegal.
        TokenCapacityExceededKernelException - if too many labels would be created by this call, compared to the token id space available.
        KernelException
